    "description": "We at Patanjali Ayurved International Enterprises are looking for an experienced Process Engineer based out of Hyderabad. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout Patanjali Ayurved International Enterprises:\nPatanjali Ayurved International Enterprises is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Manage supplier quality audits and vendor development\n• Conduct root cause analysis for quality rejections and defects\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n• Train and supervise shop floor workers and supervisors\n• Prepare production cost analysis and efficiency reports\n• Coordinate with logistics for dispatching finished goods\n• Oversee daily production operations to meet output targets\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Bachelor's degree in a relevant field\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in ERP Systems\n• Proficiency in PPAP\n• Proficiency in GD&T\n• Proficiency in SolidWorks\n• Proficiency in Lean Manufacturing\n• Proficiency in ISO 9001\n• Proficiency in Six Sigma\n• Proficiency in 5S\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Hyderabad, Telangana, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Patanjali Ayurved International Enterprises!",
